  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Those which doesn't have the [NON-ENGLISH] shall-- cannot walk on the street from this day from 5 o'clock on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They shall stay in the house, in the afternoon, in the evening, in the house.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And from-- from 5 o'clock in the morning, they should leave everything in their houses, but not the most valuable items on their-- in their rucksacks.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They can take-- they have, you know, gold or-- or what-- with clothes or whatever with them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Happened when I went back, I'm going back to the-- by getting the saccharin.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "This man, I think his name was Geller, [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Shmuluk ?] Geller.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I wish I can find him sometimes if he is alive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He left before me, and after I received the-- I-- by going back, I read that sign that we are not allowed to but-- but those who have the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So some kind of [? idea ?] when I came into the house after giving-- making a little bit of that milk for my child, I thought to myself, maybe I should go to the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's still time.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was maybe around 2 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To see, maybe there are some men like from-- who has [NON-ENGLISH], but their wives went to Russia or their wife passed away, anything can happen.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we-- I will promise to pay them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They shall include me and my child, but it can't be happened, but I never give-- I am not giving up.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If I get an-- an idea, I have to try to work it out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If I can, I can, but I have to try it even over and over.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
